[metadata]
Name=Brago Stax [Primer]
Description={"ops":[{"insert":"Brago: Blink and you'll miss it"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nHi! I'm ClydeBankston, and I've been playing Brago in one form or another for the past three or four-ish years. I firmly believe that this deck is the best competitive Brago deck out there, and has been honed over many, "},{"attributes":{"bold":true},"insert":"many "},{"insert":"hours of playtesting and goldfishing. \n\nWhy play Brago?"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"It's Azorius"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"You get to play terrible cards"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"He allows for you to have essentially double mana"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"It's stax!"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"You will not enjoy Brago if you:"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Like very consistent hands"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Like to play good cards"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Dislike stax"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Dislike the combat step"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Brago is a very inconsistent general, and is also quite weak due to the deck just "},{"attributes":{"bold":true},"insert":"not working"},{"insert":" if he's not on the board. His inconsistencies stem from a requirement of two factors to be met. An ideal hand will have a T2 Brago with a stax piece/value engine of some sort. Due to this, aggressive mulligans are often demanded and put you at a card disadvantage.\n\nAlso check out MXYZ's tempo list "},{"attributes":{"link":"https://www.moxfield.com/decks/hbLMs7xcfUyun2nxK-sRlw"},"insert":"HERE"},{"insert":"\n\n"},{"attributes":{"link":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j-njgMhh38I"},"insert":"Playing  With Power made a video about how the deck works, so watching it before carrying on reading is adviseable because they explained things very clearly."},{"insert":"\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nSo...how DO you win anyway?"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nThis was actually a very easy but complex question to answer, and Brago doesn't actually 'win' immediately after comboing off. Yet another reason why he's considered to not be the best.\n\nStrionic Resonator Loops:"},{"attributes":{"header":2},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Have "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Strionic Resonator"}},{"insert":"  on board with 2+ mana available in rocks (Not "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mox Diamond"}},{"insert":"  or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Chrome Mox"}},{"insert":" , so exclude these during your maths)"},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Swing with Brago. When combat damage is dealt, a trigger goes onto the stack."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Activate the "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Strionic Resonator"}},{"insert":"  in response to the trigger.  A copy goes onto the stack over the original. Let that resolve. Flicker the resonator and your rocks. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Remember, there is still the original trigger on the stack. Repeat Step 3 x Infinity, you have infinite blinks and most likely infinite colourless mana during your combat step. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Note: With an "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Arcum's Astrolabe"}},{"insert":" out you can filter your colourless for coloured mana.\nNote #2: All of this is happening during your combat damage step after combat damage has been dealt. YOU ARE NOT IN THE END OF COMBAT STEP. I REPEAT. YOU ARE NOT AT THE END OF COMBAT.\n\nWhy is this important?"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"This is the premier and most well known way for Brago to win. With these triggers ETBs you control will influence what paths you will take to victory. By comboing with "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Strionic Resonator"}},{"insert":" you have several ways of winning.\nIf you have an "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Arcum's Astrolabe"}},{"insert":" or a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stupefying Touch"}},{"insert":" out then you are capable of drawing infinite cards. With 2UU up your next step is to draw until you hit a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Venser, Shaper Savant"}},{"insert":" to bounce all your enemies' permanents. DO NOT DRAW OUT YOUR DECK. You do not win this turn. You'll probably want to have 10-15 cards left."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"If you have a pirate ("},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rishadan Cutpurse"}},{"insert":" or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rishadan Footpad"}},{"insert":"), "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Venser, Shaper Savant"}},{"insert":" then you can get rid of all your opponents' permanents, as compared to "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":" which only hits nonland permanents."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\nWhen your opponents have no permanents in play:"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":" Cast a  "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinisphere"}},{"insert":" or a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":" to lock them out off the game. If your opponents don't concede then you have to play the game out. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Your opponents haven't conceded to a hard lock.  Now you much consider the route to victory. The first priority is to get "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tezzeret the Seeker"}},{"insert":" into play. His ult wins you the game quickly (because Brago beats in a timed environment just sucks and is pretty pointless). If you don't have a Tezzeret in your deck/or the field then you should ignore the next two steps and just play creatures and beat your opponents to death."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Spend 1/2 turns just playing out artifacts and, if possible, assemble "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rings of Brighthearth"}},{"insert":" + "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Basalt Monolith"}},{"insert":" to play out your artifacts in one turn. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"When you have enough artifacts out, ult "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tezzeret the Seeker"}},{"insert":" and swing for lethal with your artifact army and win. To know exactly how many to play one should play out a general rule is to divide your opponents' combined life totals by five."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\nIn our list we have  "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rings of Brighthearth"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Basalt Monolith"}},{"insert":" as mentioned above, but we also run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sensei's Divining Top"}},{"insert":". This is a situational grab. It's really only used in order to draw into the Resonator.\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nStax"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nStax is the gameplan of this deck. Brago couples with artifact stax particularly well due to his blinking. Things like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Static Orb"}},{"insert":" don't matter since your rocks get blinked and enter untapped, ready for another use. Let's just go through the list, shall we?\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Aura of Silence"}},{"insert":": It taxes your opponents from playing rocks. It can also get rid of a pesky "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stony Silence"}},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Aven Mindcensor"}},{"insert":": It stops hulk. It stops Yisan. It stops fetches. Enough said."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Back to Basics"}},{"insert":": We play Azorius so our fetches just grab basics. It's very detrimental to 3+ colour decks (also known as most cEDH decks)."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Cursed Totem"}},{"insert":": We have no creature abilities. I see this as an absolute win."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Drannith Magistrate"}},{"insert":" : This card is nuts. Clearly nobody realised that this stops generals from being cast. That's bonkers in and of itself, stopping not only a random "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tymna the Weaver"}},{"insert":" but also stuff like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":"  or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Godo, Bandit Warlord"}},{"insert":". Because this card just isn't good enough, it is a brick wall for "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Kess, Dissident Mage"}},{"insert":" . Think "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grafdigger's Cage"}},{"insert":"  on crack. "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Ethersworn Canonist"}},{"insert":": Most of our cards are artifacts and it stops storm/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Food Chain"}},{"insert":". "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grafdigger's Cage"}},{"insert":": It stops reanimator builds and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":", I like it."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grasp of Fate"}},{"insert":": It's just good since it is a 3 for 1 card and we always take the best thing."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Narset, Parter of Veils"}},{"insert":": It generates card advantage, gets blinked by Brago, and stops unfair things. Did I mention it's one-sided?"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Wave"}},{"insert":": It stops general-based decks like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"The Gitrog Monster"}},{"insert":" or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":" and gets blinked by Brago to reset the counters. Good in the same way "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grasp of Fate"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Oblivion Ring"}},{"insert":" are good. It's targeted, recurring, removal."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Pithing Needle"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Phyrexian Revoker"}},{"insert":" are situational \"Turn that thing off\" cards. They are just very good, almost never a dead draw. With "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Pithing Needle"}},{"insert":" you can also turn off fetches."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rest in Peace"}},{"insert":": The best graveyard hate piece in the game."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinisphere"}},{"insert":" are good locks post-combo and we don't really care about them because of our abundance of mana."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stasis"}},{"insert":": The best stax piece we have in the deck tied with "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tangle Wire"}},{"insert":". It exists forever due to our ability to blink coloured mana rocks over and over again in order to pay for it "},{"attributes":{"bold":true},"insert":"FOREVER"},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":" "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Static Orb"}},{"insert":": Amazing, pairs well with "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tangle Wire"}},{"insert":". We have lots of artifact mana which can be blinked and Brago gives our creatures psuedo-vigilance."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Winter Orb"}},{"insert":": Great card, we have lots of artifact mana."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nGeneral Tips/Knowledge"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nThis is just about good stuff and ways to use it.\nWith "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Enlightened Tutor"}},{"insert":"  in your opening hand, keep that hand. Turn One tutor for a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mana Crypt"}},{"insert":", then get a Turn 2 Brago out. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"If you cast a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinket Mage"}},{"insert":" then generally that grabs either a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mana Crypt"}},{"insert":" or an "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Arcum's Astrolabe"}},{"insert":". Typically you should grab Crypt, however, if you have a bunch of rocks then grab the Astrolabe. It also allows for a cheeky Resonator topdeck to win the game."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"When casting "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trophy Mage"}},{"insert":", generally I take a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tangle Wire"}},{"insert":", blink it, then grab a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Static Orb"}},{"insert":". I find this more impactful on my opponents than getting "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rings of Brighthearth"}},{"insert":"+"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Basalt Monolith"}},{"insert":". Another way  to go is to grab a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Basalt Monolith"}},{"insert":" and a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tangle Wire"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Static Orb"}},{"insert":" because that at least lets you cast stuff."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tezzeret the Seeker"}},{"insert":" is the best card in your deck. ALWAYS minus him since, after getting blinked, he is considered a 'new' card and therefore can be down-ticked again, or essentially twice in a turn. It's really good. With Tezzeret an early...TANGLE WIRE can just lock down the game. Remember, with Tezzeret you can always -0 for a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mana Crypt"}},{"insert":". Did I mention he's amazing?"},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tezzeret the Seeker"}},{"insert":" can also, in a pinch, grab "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rings of Brighthearth"}},{"insert":" first. Then you flicker and -3. In response pay 2 mana from the "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rings of Brighthearth"}},{"insert":" trigger to copy it. Grab "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Basalt Monolith"}},{"insert":"  and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sensei's Divining Top"}},{"insert":". Now you can draw your deck and all that goodly goodness."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"When in doubt grab "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tangle Wire"}},{"insert":". It's a really good card in this deck, and one of my favourite pieces to use."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"If you have Resonator combo in hand and a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Recruiter of the Guard"}},{"insert":" in play you can 'win' by grabbing Venser with it. It also sets up a lock because you can grab "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trophy Mage"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tribute Mage"}},{"insert":"->"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinisphere"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":" for the lock."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"With "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Lightning Greaves"}},{"insert":" on Brago you can't blink him, so keep that in mind. This also means that you can't achieve a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stasis"}},{"insert":" lock with Greaves on him. If you have greaves on Brago but want to achieve a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stasis"}},{"insert":" lock then out them onto one of your hatebears pre-combat, blink, then put them back onto Brago."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"ALWAYS ATTACK THE BLACK PLAYER. Just do it on principle. If there's multiple then just keep smacking and pray you chose correctly. This is because many black decks run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Ad Nauseam"}},{"insert":" and/or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Necropotence"}},{"insert":". This requires a bit of meta-specific knowledge because many decks don't run these cards anymore."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"It may feel good to "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Gilded Drake"}},{"insert":" a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tymna the Weaver"}},{"insert":", but overall that's never really the play. It's just really greedy. Besides, it gives an opponent a FLYING BLOCKER for Brago so whatever you're draking should be 100% worth it."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Containment Priest"}},{"insert":" is an interesting card. On our opponent's side it will cause Brago and whatever other creatures we have to be exiled. On our side it can be blinked alongside our permanents and will not exile those other things."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nFlex Slots"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nIn this deck there are about 4 flex slots which you can alter to tune this deck to your meta. They are essentially as follows.\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grafdigger's Cage"}},{"insert":" "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":" and/or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grasp of Fate"}},{"insert":" "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grafdigger's Cage"}},{"insert":" in a post-Hulk world is there to stop reanimator decks and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":". Also, "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Kess, Dissident Mage"}},{"insert":". What was once an autoinclude is now a situational stax piece. You don't lose much for playing it when it stops unfair stuff."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":" is a pretty alright card. It exiles things but if multiple people play "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tymna the Weaver"}},{"insert":" I would understand cutting it (because it gives the Tymna player more creatures to attack with and draw cards)."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\nTo tune this for your meta (as you should, since stax is pretty bad without some tuning) the following cards should be added in. \n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Relic of Progenitus"}},{"insert":" if against mainly decks like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"The Gitrog Monster"}},{"insert":" or reanimator builds such as "},{"attributes":{"link":"https://www.moxfield.com/decks/CwZ4jijMkkWpvx7smX2-jQ"},"insert":"Razakats"},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Anje Falkenrath"}},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Teferi, Time Raveler"}},{"insert":" (T3feri) if in a counter-heavy meta or one where Brago is one of the faster decks since it bounces stuff+draws a card every turn. I wouldn't run this in a combo-centric meta. If you are in a T2-3 meta (Tazri, Scion, etc) then this is the card for you!"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rule of Law"}},{"insert":" if you play in a meta where the only real archetypes are storm and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Food Chain"}},{"insert":". Other that that there's no reason to run it since it hurts our game-winning turn and use of blinked rocks."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run Mom ("},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mother of Runes"}},{"insert":") if your meta has consistent single-target removal. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Giver of Runes"}},{"insert":"  isn't quite as good but will essentially serve the same purpose. Remember to "},{"attributes":{"bold":true},"insert":"not"},{"insert":" blink them because if you do they will have summoning sickness."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Containment Priest"}},{"insert":"  "},{"attributes":{"strike":true},"insert":"in a very Hulk heavy meta"},{"insert":" (imagine having to tech against hulk) if your meta is filled with  decks cheating mana costs. Some of these decks include reanimator decks ("},{"attributes":{"link":"https://www.moxfield.com/decks/CwZ4jijMkkWpvx7smX2-jQ"},"insert":"Razakats"},{"insert":", Anje, "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Varolz, the Scar-Striped"}},{"insert":"), Yisan and, of course, BRAGO."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"If your meta is filled with too many "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Opposition Agent"}},{"insert":"s then I'd recommend running "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Pongify"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rapid Hybridization"}},{"insert":", or even both but that could easily become too overkill."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Wave"}},{"insert":"  if you have too many general-focused strategies in your meta. The card is very slow and can often be pretty bad."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":" if your meta devolves into nothing but "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":" and creature-based scepter decks. Otherwise it's very slow."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Run "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Pongify"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rapid Hybridization"}},{"insert":", or both should your meta devolve into creature-dependent decks like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Najeela, the Blade-Blossom"}},{"insert":" and/or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Opposition Agent"}},{"insert":" in every other person's deck."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nWhy don't you run..."},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Shimmer Myr"}},{"insert":"? Shimmer Myr certainly has a place in some Brago decks as an enabler for infinite coloured mana if you have access to card draw during your combat phase, but it's too dead of a draw outside of this.  If you are in topdeck mode then it truly does nothing and is almost never a welcome sight outside of its niche use in the combat step. "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Walking Ballista"}},{"insert":"? Walking Ballista and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Shimmer Myr"}},{"insert":" was something I toyed around with for a while, but at the end of the day it isn't consistent at all. It enabled us to win in one turn after comboing off but instead made us run dead cards, something this deck can't really afford to do already because of its place in the meta. It's yet another dead draw, though could be transformed into a decently sized beater if we had nothing else to do with our rocks. We don't need these alternate wincons because once we have a lock then your opponents physically cannot do more than play a fetch and crack it."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Helm of Obedience"}},{"insert":"? We just don't need Helm of Obedience. Our wincons are alright as they are and, although "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grand Arbiter Augustin IV"}},{"insert":" and some Control Zur builds utilise the combo we have better options. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Strionic Resonator"}},{"insert":" wins are infinitely more preferable and efficient, though if you have to run this I guess that's fine.  I'm not a fan, personally."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Isochron Scepter"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Dramatic Reversal"}},{"insert":"? With no real way to abuse Dramatic Scepter in the command zone like CST decks just...just don't do it. Dramatic Reversal on its own may be fine if used strictly as a blue ritual or something like that. With the printing of "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Lithoform Engine"}},{"insert":" it  may be viable but, like I said, we don't have a reliable outlet."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Archaeomancer"}},{"insert":"? For those who don't know, Archaeomancer enables several different combos as well as being a value engine. "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"With cards such as "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Time Warp"}},{"insert":" or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Capture of Jingzhou"}},{"insert":" it is possible to achieve infinite turns by casting the extra turn spell, blinking "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Archaeomancer"}},{"insert":" to get back the extra turn spell, then rinse and repeat until you win through beats. "},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Alternatively you could lock players out of their own turn or protect your own using "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Silence"}},{"insert":", but as we aren't a fast combo deck it really wasn't that great. In a "},{"attributes":{"link":"https://youtu.be/6clUWjcvBYE?t=966"},"insert":"PWP video this lock was shown"},{"insert":", but that's probably better in a more traditional control/fast combo build similar to "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grand Arbiter Augustin IV"}},{"insert":". This is a great card to use if people want to build a staxless Brago shell. Not recommended, but probably one of the better options here. It's also 4cmc. If you create a deck more similar to MXYZ's list then this is fringe usable."},{"attributes":{"list":"ordered"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grand Arbiter Augustin IV"}},{"insert":"? It's a slightly better "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":" which decreases the cost of our general. It is 4cmc though, and generally speaking we want to have an incredibly low average cmc. To me the effect just isn't worth it but if you are playing in a slower meta then go for it."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Hierophant's Chalice"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mortarpod"}},{"insert":"? These just don't do it for me, the argument is very similar to that of running Ballista/Shimmer Myr. They just aren't great."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":"? Linvala is great but it doesn't stop as much nowadays. It's slow and clunky, as well as competing with Brago as a four drop. You can play it if you have a meta filled with "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Captain Sisay"}},{"insert":" or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":" but it's still very slow."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Wave"}},{"insert":"  or "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Tide"}},{"insert":"? Parallax Wave is the better of the two but both are 4cmc which, as has been said before, competes with Brago. They  are also very slow. In the case of Parallax Wave it can help against generals like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"The Gitrog Monster"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Yisan, the Wanderer Bard"}},{"insert":", and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Godo, Bandit Warlord"}},{"insert":" to ensure they cannoy do anything but it's a pretty niche card which is oftentimes not good. Parallax Tide is just bad. Don't run it in a competitive deck."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"More nonbasic lands? Stuff like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Reflecting Pool"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"City of Brass"}},{"insert":", and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mana Confluence"}},{"insert":"? I just don't like nonbasic lands. In a two colour deck we're fine with essentially just fetches and basics. Some stuff is too good to not have like the two fetchable dual lands we are currently running. Having less nonbasics also means that we are more resistant to "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Blood Moon"}},{"insert":" effects and also to "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Back to Basics"}},{"insert":". It's really all a matter of preference."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nBudget Replacements"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nIn place of the expensive rocks ("},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mox Diamond"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mana Crypt"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grim Monolith"}},{"insert":", and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mox Opal"}},{"insert":") you should put in the 2cmc rocks like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mind Stone"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Prismatic Lens"}},{"insert":", and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Thought Vessel"}},{"insert":".  (Also possibly "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Fractured Powerstone"}},{"insert":") This will really hamper the power of "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinket Mage"}},{"insert":" so I'd consider just taking him out in favour of a hate bear if you are going down this road. Even "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Fractured Powerstone"}},{"insert":" is alright if you are on a budget and I'd certainly play it before something like "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Gilded Lotus"}},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Reshape"}},{"insert":"  is a cheaper but also 'fixed' "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Transmute Artifact"}},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Fetches and duals can be replaced with basics if necessary."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"If Snow-Covered lands are too expensive/outside your budget then "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Arcum's Astrolabe"}},{"insert":"  can be replaced with a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Prophetic Prism"}},{"insert":"."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"The more expensive stax pieces ("},{"insert":{"card-link":"Static Orb"}},{"insert":", "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":", and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinisphere"}},{"insert":") can be replaced with cantrips to help you dig or yet more bears. It is quite crucial to get your hands on a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Sphere of Resistance"}},{"insert":"  and/or a "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trinisphere"}},{"insert":" ASAP in order to ensure victory after comboing."},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nUpdates"},{"attributes":{"header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n"},{"attributes":{"underline":true},"insert":"Kaldheim"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Kaldheim has give us "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Weathered Runestone"}},{"insert":", an interesting card which is one one mana more than "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Grafdigger's Cage"}},{"insert":"  and does quite a lot more than it. Unfortunately, this increase in power comes at the cost of one mana so it's not goin into the main list. The main reason for this is that Turn Two, I find, is either devoted to holding up counterspells or ramping with something like an "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Azorius Signet"}},{"insert":", setting up a Turn 3 Brago. If you play in a slower meta then  Weathered Runestone is an automatic upgrade but I can't justify putting it into the main list.\n\nWith the format getting quicker, those of us in the Discord server came to the conclusion that more interaction was needed, hence the inclusion of both FOW and FON. This allows us to  play a more wild game and tap out for Brago whilst carrying answers. We decided to take out "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Wave"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":"  because they  are slow and had been lagging behind for quite some time. Doing this takes out two flex slots and, consequently, makes Brago even more optimised.\n\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Force of Will"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Force of Negation"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Parallax Wave"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Weathered Runestone"}},{"insert":" to the mayboard"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"underline":true},"insert":"Commander Legends"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Commander Legends has granted us "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Jeweled Lotus"}},{"insert":". This adds to the possibility of more T1 or T2 Bragos and gives the possibility of more speed to keep up with an ever-more competitive and focused metagame. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Delay"}},{"insert":" isn't the best counterspell in the world and has been underperforming for some time.\n\nWith the release of "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Opposition Agent"}},{"insert":", spot removal is being made more and more necessary. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Pongify"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Rapid Hybridization"}},{"insert":" are being added to the Mayboard as meta-specific options in place of other flex slots.\n"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"underline":true},"insert":"Zendikar Rising"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"Zendikar Rising has been released and with it comes "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Lithoform Engine"}},{"insert":" and "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":", two amazing cards. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Lithoform Engine"}},{"insert":" is a second "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Strionic Resonator"}},{"insert":"  which may also open the way  for "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Isochron Scepter"}},{"insert":"/"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Dramatic Reversal"}},{"insert":" loops. This is turning out to be a pretty good day. I'm taking out "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mystical Tutor"}},{"insert":"  because it doesn't really do much.\n\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":" actually just removes cards from the game and gives people blockers on the ground. I don't see much wrong with this. It's going in, "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Oblivion Ring"}},{"insert":"  is coming out because it just doesn't pull its own weight.\n\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Lithoform Engine"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Skyclave Apparition"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Mystical Tutor"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Oblivion Ring"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"underline":true},"insert":"FLASH IS BANNED"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"FLASH IS BANNED EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY. Also, we have all these cool cards from C20 and Ikoria. Most of these cards are pretty irrelevant, but we have a free counterspell so that's neat. Also, now that the king is dead, "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Thassa's Oracle"}},{"insert":"  and Consult will be the premier way to win. Enter: The grindfest.\n\nObviously, all "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stifle"}},{"insert":" effects out. We got some cool cards, one in IKO and the other from C20. "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Drannith Magistrate"}},{"insert":"  is an INTERESTING card to say the least. This card really messes over Brago but also messes over every other EDH deck out there. It's a good hatebear. If Oracle continues to be a huge problem then I may cut a counterspell for Stifle but we'll see. Mostly I'm just happy to get this anti-hulk tech out.\n\nWe also got "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Fierce Guardianship"}},{"insert":" . It's a free counterspell and we always want to have Brago on the battlefield.  I can't really say many bad things about it. I'm 100% playing this over other free counterspells like The Force's or Pact because this has more flexibility. A three cmc counterspell with the potential to be free is pretty alright.\n\nFinally,  we're adding back in "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":". With the boogeyman gone we can afford to play a four drop. We don't play creatures with activated abilities like, well, GREEN so we're fine.\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Stifle"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tale's End"}},{"insert":" out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Trickbind"}},{"insert":"  out "},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Drannith Magistrate"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Fierce Guardianship"}},{"insert":"  in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"underline":true},"insert":"Theros Beyond Death"},{"attributes":{"header":3},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"So...fish hulk. We could typically be alright with hulk but now we have to have an answer. I'm adding in "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tale's End"}},{"insert":" to have three ways to interact with it. At this point I'm not comfortable tapping out T2 unless it's for Brago. For this I'm taking out "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":" because it doesn't stop Shuffle Hulk and in my meta it's just Yisan atm. I'd rather keep things up for fish hulk. Also lowers our curve.\n\nWe also got a great card selector with "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Omen of the Sea"}},{"insert":". IMHO it's better than "},{"insert":{"card-link":"Oath of Jace"}},{"insert":". It also has flash so we can hold up mana T2. All in all pretty decent. I'm still testing it, so will update if it doesn't do so well. It also means that if you have infinite coloured mana during the combat phase generally you can't deck yourself if you flash it in then start sculpting your hand.\n\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Tale's End"}},{"insert":" in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Omen of the Sea"}},{"insert":" in"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Oath of Jace"}},{"insert":"  out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":{"card-link":"Linvala, Keeper of Silence"}},{"insert":" out"},{"attributes":{"list":"bullet"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nWell that's all from me, so if you have any questions just put them below and I'll be happy to help. Alternatively I'm reasonably active playing Cockatrice under the name,  well,  ClydeBankston.\n\nFinally, please join the Brago discord. It's a generic Brago discord, supporting all forms of Brago and levels of optimisation.\n\nhttps://discord.gg/ZkX5uQ8\n"}]}
